figgy.title: Document where things are backed up and where they can be restored from.
Make Bulk Ingest for ephemera boxes/projects more closely aligned to scanned resource bulk ingest in Figgy

comments.body:
What they're doing now:
`ssh deploy@lib-proc6 "cd /opt/figgy/current; RAILS_ENV=production bundle exec rake figgy:lae:ingest_disk_files "'/mnt/diglibdata/pudl/lae_to_ingest/321010xxxxx'""`

This calls IngestLaeFolderJob, which calls BulkIngestService. I think the key difference is it passes `property: :barcode` and the bulk ingest UI can't do that.

There's also no way to get to a bulk ingest UI right now that creates Folders.

Currently this allows for ingesting images from a single box with multiple folders. Using Figgy, only individual folders can be ingested. Latest use case is IRC material, which has delivered 75 boxes-worth of folders and images. Testing ways to use above code to ingest 75 boxes in bulk, but may have to use the code to ingest each box separately (75 ingests).
